HEADWORD: Utilize
<hw>U"til*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Utilized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Utilizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>utiliser</ets>.]</ety> <def>To make useful; to turn to profitable
account or use; to make use of; <as>as, to <ex>utilize</ex> the whole
power of a machine; to <ex>utilize</ex> one's
opportunities</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In former ages, the mile-long corridors, with their numerous
alcoves, might have been <qex>utilized</qex> as . . . dungeons.</q>
<rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uti possidetis</ent>⟦br⟧
